Write a python program to perform addition of 2 number and display the addition on screen as a result

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Step 1 : Start
Step 2 : Define a variable with a value = number1
Step 3 : Define a variable with a value = number2
Step 4 : Perform Addition
Step 5 : Store result of addtion
Step 6 : Display result on screen
Step 7 : Exit/Stop

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Identifier Rules

1) It may only contain letters (uppercase or lowercase), numbers or the underscore character (_).
2) It may not start with a number.
3) It may not be a keyword.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Identifier Names - Guidelines

1) Be Descriptive
	- variable name should describe the contents of the variable.
	- a function name must indicate what the function does.
2) Don't use abbreviations unnecessarily - they may be ambiguous and more difficult to read.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

---> Difference between a function and method

Function - It is always indepedent. Grouping statements together to avoid code duplication

Method - It is always bound to the class.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

---> See the list of builtins in Python

dir(__builtins__)

---> See the built-in methods of a class (string in this case)

dir(str)

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Boolean

1) int
	other than 0 ---> True
	0 ---> False

2) float
	other than 0.0 ---> True
	0.0 ---> False

3) str
	other than (Empty String) "" ---> True
	(Empty String) "" ---> False

Boolean Precedence

1) ()
2) **
3) *,/,% +,-
4) <,<=,>,>=,==,!=
5) is,is not
6) not
7) and
8) or

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Collections

1) List - mutable

2) Tuple

3) Sets

4) Ranges

5) Dictionaries

